             <h1 style="font-family: 'Arial Black'; background-color: #FFFFFF; border-style: solid">INSTRUCTIONS OF PERMIT FOR EXCAVATION WORK</h1>
        <ol>
 <li>This permit is applicable in all digging work in side factories premises. </li>
 <li>If any person starts any excavation work firstly initiate this permit and take clearance from all departments.</li>
 <li>A person who initiate any excavation work he will initiate PTW for excavation work.</li>
 <li>Make all safety arrangements for excavation work (Barricading, lighting , safe access, safe vehicle entry).</li>
 <li>Display caution Board near excavation site.</li>
 <li>Excavated material shall be away from edge of excavated area.</li>
 <li>For proper access provide a good ladder.</li>
 <li>A person must supervise the excavation activity.</li>
 <li>All person involved in excavation work should be trained and TBT of all done by initiator.</li>
 <li>If any other hazard found during work, Stop work immediately and take necessary action.</li>
 <li>Ensure use of all required PPEs for worker (Safety helmet, gumboot, dust mask, goggle).</li>
 <li>Sloping the sides of the excavation to an angle not steeper than 1½:1 (for every foot of depth, the trench must be excavated back 1½ feet). A slope of this gradation is safe for any type of soil.</li>
 <li>Keep excavated soil (spoils) and other materials at least 2 feet (0.61 meters) from trench edges.</li>
 <li>Do not work under suspended or raised loads and materials.</li>
 <li>Inspect trenches at the start of each shift.</li>
 <li>Inspect trenches following a rainstorm or other water intrusion. </li>
 <li>Inspect trenches after any occurrence that could have changed conditions in the trench.</li>
 <li>Where vehicle have to Tip material into excavation, use stop Block to prevent them forover running.</li>
</ol>
